Class HBaseMapFamilyPager

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, Iterator<KijiRowData>, KijiPager
@ApiAudience.Private
public final class HBaseMapFamilyPager
extends Object
implements KijiPager

HBase implementation of KijiPager for map-type families.

This pager lists the qualifiers in the map-type family and nothing else. In particular, the cells content is not retrieved.

This pager conforms to the KijiPager interface, in order to implement KijiRowData.getPager(String). More straightforward interfaces are available using HBaseQualifierPager and HBaseQualifierIterator.

See Also:
HBaseQualifierPager, HBaseQualifierIterator

next

public KijiRowData next()
Fetches the next page of cells from the Kiji table using the configured page size.
  • The page size is an upper bound to the number of cells retrieved from the table.
  • The page may contain fewer cells than the specified page size. In particular, the page can sometimes be empty, even though more pages follow.
    • Use Iterator.hasNext() to determine if more pages follow.
